Clients will now be able to communicate with their customers in their own language and within their own context thanks to Lelapa AI’s new product called Vulavula. This app focuses on under-represented languages. Lelapa AI team hopes to make a change in the country using artificial intelligence to improve sectors such as agriculture, education, healthcare and energy. VulaVula offers digital support for underrepresented languages. It does this by providing NLP as a service for multiple languages ​​and for specific areas of concentration. Features include multilingual NER, intent recognition, transcription and translation. In the video below Lelapa AI CEO Pelonomi Moiloa and COO Jade Abbott share more about the applications: 